                <p style="margin-bottom: 3rem; font-size: 20px; line-height: 2; color: #f1f5f9;">Now here's where things get frustrating. Most of the popular stem splitting tools out there - la la la AI, Ultimate Vocal Remover, Vocal Remover - they're okay for basic stuff, but they have some serious limitations that nobody talks about.</p>

                <p style="margin-bottom: 3rem; font-size: 20px; line-height: 2; color: #f1f5f9;">The biggest issue is that they don't maintain the quality you need for serious analysis. They'll compress the dynamic range, introduce weird artifacts, and worst of all, the stems don't perfectly align with the original track when you add them back together. That's a massive problem if you're trying to do precise mixing work.</p>

